messages.content: Polaris knocks on the door with their free hand, their other holding too many bags to seem possible to care.
...they knock again.
(( @dirt.eater if u dont mind 🥺
Malachite opens the door and grins, green tinted spectacles glinting.
Polaris smiles at Malachite back, holding up the hand of.... 15 or so bags of groceries.
“Did a little shopping for you,” they say
"Haha, epic."
They hummed. “Can I come in?”

"Oh! Yeah. Thanks."
They wink under their tinted lenses and grab a few of the bags, stepping back to let Polaris through the door.

Polaris frowns at that. They didn’t need any help with the bags... Regardless, they enter the house and head to the kitchen room, first bringing out some tea and preparing it in the boiler so that it gets ready while they’re putting away the groceries.
“It’s caramel.. I hope that’s ok,” they hum.
They refuse to drink boiled mountain dew again.

Malachite wrinkles their nose at that, then shrugs.
"Don't think I've tried that flavor, I usually just get green tea. It might be good though."
“Yeah. It’s my favorite,” they smile softly, grabbing groceries out of the bag to put them away.
Some plants, like apples, lettuce, plums, peaches, cherries, etc, some meats like chicken or beef, and some other stuff like cheese, cream cheese, milk, pita chips, etc etc.
...General stuff. Polaris’s suspicions were confirmed when they opened up some cabinets to see them almost completely empty.
“...Malachite.”
"Hmm?"
“Why do you not buy enough food...”
*And I mean real food, not just doritos and mountain dew,* they don’t add, turning to look at Malachite with a pokerface.

"I- I buy real food!" 
Malachite protests, gesturing at some wilting spinach.
"I just... usually get takeout!"
“That’s not healthy..” Polaris frowns, concerned.
Polaris quiets for a second, thinking.
“If you want, you can just- u-uh, come over to my place for meals..”
“Since you don’t eat healthy ones yourself,” they add to that, their cheeks slightly glowing brighter. Because, you know, bright ass violet blush.
Theres a knock at the door! Please let them in

Malachite sets down the bottle of soda they were putting away and lean in to set their hand on Polaris' shoulder.
"I'd like that-"
They smile, before being cut off by a sharp knock.
"Oh shit- hold on, I'll get that."
Polaris nods, turning their face and blushing harder than before. They continue putting groceries in the fridge
Malachite saunters over to the door and opens it.
Argenti brought escargot
"Oh, *fuck* yeah."

Seriya is at the door, With Argenti! He waves. “Good day Malachite! I hope i didnt interrupt anything. I brought mostly sweets.” Seriya reaches into his bag and pulls out a huge jar of caramel popcorn.
Polaris is suffering, but puts away the last groceries in time for the teapot to finish. Taking it off the stove, they search for mugs
.........because Polaris doesn’t drink tea in tea cups. For some odd reason.

"Nice, thanks!" 
Malachite holds the door open for them and goes back to the kitchen to keep helping Polaris with the groceries.
"I also brought Croissants."
Seriya walks in, and sets down the jar of Caramel popcorn and a concerning amount of chocolate on a nearby table. They give a thumbs up to the kitchen.
Polaris already finished with the groceries, but they’re struggling to find teacups and mugs..

"Oh! Cups are in here."
Malachite opens a cabinet to reveal a variety of mismatched mugs, most of them covered in paint.

“...i’m getting you new cups, too.” Polaris starts grabbing four of the mugs, taking them all to the sink to generally clean out what gunk is in there, since Polaris doesn’t even know the last time these were washed.
Agrenti got himself choccy milk. Because he's epic.

"Hey, I *like* my mugs."
They frown, picking up a chipped frog mug.
“They’re nice, but... use some for paint, and others for drinking. Don’t use them all for both,” Polaris explains, cleaning out the mugs they grabbed and pouring tea into them.
“I don’t want you to poison yourself..” they mumble.

"...I haven't died yet."
Malachite flicks a paint chip off of the frog mug with their manicured fingernail.
"And I like my froggy mug."
Polaris grabs it out of their hand. “Let me fix it then— or at the very least, let me scrub the paint off of it.”

"Hey-" 
Malachite grabs at the mug indignantly.
“...” Polaris keeps their grip on the mug.

Malachite pauses, then sets their free hand on Polaris' and gives them a pleading look.
"Give me my fucking froggy mug."
“Let me clean it first, you weirdo..” they mumbled, trying to tug it away.
Argenti chuckled

"Fuck you." 
Malachite tries to lick their face, but cannot, as they are a full two feet taller. He huffs and goes back to putting away bottles of soda.
Polaris gives a small triumphant smile and goes to the sink to clean the mug (especially the crack) and scrub off the paint. Because, you know, they care
Afterwards, they poured the tea into each cup (yes, that includes the froggy cup) and set them down on the coffee table in front of the couch.
“Have you guys ever watched our part before?”
“Huh? No, we only got to the start of Mr.Joestar’s part. Thank you Polaris.” Seriya doesnt touch his cup, but he is still grateful.
"Jonathan was a good man..."
“...” Polaris says nothing, but silently agrees as they take their own cup and sip out of it, sitting to the very right of the couch, nearest spot to the kitchen
“Our part doesn’t spoil anything about Gigi’s part, so don’t worry about that,” Polaris turned to Malachite. “Where’s the disc for Stardust Crusaders again?”
"Stardust Crusaders? Is that like our team name?"
“...Our part name. Gigi’s is Battle Tendency.”
“Thats cute.” Seriya gives a thumbs up at their part name.

"Uhhh..."
Malachite thinks for a moment, then gestures to a container underneath the television.
"I think it's in there."
“わかた,” they confirmed, going to grab the tapes. Grabbing the box of part 3 discs and taking out the one for the first quarter of it, they put it in the player and press play.
...Polaris also prays to god that the others don’t care too much for how much of a dramatic bitch Jotaro was.
Argenti looks back at the first time Polnareff met Iggy
"That mutt was a stupid smelly bastard. I miss him."
“...There are worlds where we all live,” Polaris comments, sensing the loneliness in Argenti.
"Must've been nice."
“...yeah,” Polaris almost smiles. Almost. “It was.”
As the TV starts playing, Polaris has to look away during Jotaro’s introduction scene.
.............*Why did I have to be so dramatic there..*
Argenti sees the Speedwagon foundation guys and knows their origin now.

“The universe is... weird. Multiple alternate realities exist— a lot of them feel like one of us just wished it would happen, and it did. In one reality, Star Platinum was Speedwagon’s soul reincarnated. Freaked Gigi out a lot,” Polaris smiles at the memory. It’s not common they think of the good in their missions.
"I can imagine star platinum with that Odd-job hat."
“...He never got a hat?” Polaris didn’t get the joke.
"Speedwagon had that Odd-job hat with the razor blades and stuff."
“..oh.” They just got the joke
"Did you ever watch James Bond movies?"
“Who’s James Bond?” Oh honey
"Oh my God. Polnareff was such a big fan of those movies. They were about this smooth talking spy. Agent 007. Bond. James Bond." He said that last part overly dramatically on purpose
“Is... Is that why you always introduced yourself as ‘Polnareff. Jean Pierre Polnareff”?”
"It was cool and you know it."
“It wasn’t. I was annoyed,” *I literally asked you to go away the first time I ever met you, and we weren’t even muns at the time...*
The next episode started as 2 mischievous brothers were shown
Argenti pointed to Oingo's outfit
“...What the fuck are those two wearing.”
"That was what you were wearing!"
Polaris stared at Argenti with a really disgusted look.
It was then Oingo revealed he could change his face with his stand
Argenti didn't put the 2 together
“Argenti. That isn’t me.”
"Obviously. That's a stand user I don't recognize."
And then the restaurant scene happened
"Oh so THAT'S what was happening!"
“Argenti. Argenti, holy shit.”
"Be quiet, this is all new to me."
“You were the one that was—! Hm. Nevermind.”
And then the scene came when Oingo planted the orange bomb in the car and had to change his face to Jotaro
It was then that it clicked
"Oh my God. Oh my fucking God."
Polaris got up. “I’m going to use the restroom.”
Seriya has just been snacking on the popcorn they made during all of this. Crunch.....
Argenti paused the episode and let everything sink in

Malachite pushes their tinted glasses onto their head and looks at Argenti. They blink at him a few times.
"You *vapid thot.* You didn't fucking notice that??"
"Look at his fucking hat! What the fuck!"
((YOU **VAPID THOT**
((IM GOING TO CRY. IM PHYSICALLY AND AUDIBLY LAUGHING
((THIS ISNT JUST A “LOL *BREATHS HARD*” SITUATION IM ACTUALLY LAUGHING

"I thought he was just having an off day!"
“Malachite dont call him that. But yeah it is pretty stupid that you didnt notice that Argenti.” Seriya just nods along
Malachite throws caramel corn into Argenti's hair.
Argenti frantically cleaned the corn out if his hair
"I mean it's nice to know who the 2 other Egyptian God users were."

"You just- you thought that was Jotaro? I'm too fucking disappointed to laugh."

Polaris comes back from the restroom
"Polaris, Mala is bullying me."

“That guy could have really hurt you guys. He almost blew your ass up— the fact that you didn’t notice them feels ridiculous.”
"We did!" Just as the characters on TV pointed out his change in clothes

“...Let’s just move onto the next episode.”

“Yes. Thank you Polaris” seriya gives a thumbs up as he pops a chocolate into his mouth.
Other than "Why didn't I use Chariot's armor technique more?"

*"Jotaro* sat by my bedside and probably held hands with me or something. Because he was a GOOD FRIEND." 
Malachite tosses more popcorn at Argenti
“..........” *I mean.. I did hold his hand... I don’t think it was because of that but I did hold it..*

The magnet episode

“Uh..do you need anything..?” Seriya looks back at  polaris. Not knowing-OH GOD. Seriya, to protect his dignity just gets up and walks to the bathroom to hide out. Not today.

"Oh thank God Abdul and Joseph separa-" he was cut off by Joseph and Abdul being pulled back together in a much more...intimate position than before
"Heyyy Polaris?"

Polaris tugged Seriya back onto the couch before releasing their grip and turning to Malachite. “?”

"Is there a universe where Jotaro and Kakyoin end up like this?" 
He waggles his eyebrows and gives him an exaggerated wink. Wink wink. Nudge nudge.
“Polaris this is too embarrassing for me to watch.” Since they couldnt escape, Seriya has just resorted to plugging his ears and closing his eyes.
“!?” Polaris’ face goes bright purple and they subconsciously reach for their ‘cap’ before remembering they don’t have one and instead covering their eyes their hand.
*YEAH BUT I DON’T EXACTLY WANNA SAY IT*
Malachite cackles gleefully.
Asshole.
"You didn't answer the question, Lariiii."
Polaris moved their hand enough to reveal at least one eye, peering at Malachite, as they nodded their head and then proceeded to cover their entire face with both hands.

Malachite makes a big deal out of scooting closer and leaning against Polaris. He grabs their arm and flutters his luminous eyelashes at them.
"Huh... how did things work out?"
“...Argenti. Help.”
The sequence had long since ended but Argenti hadn't taken his hands off his face
Star Platinum grabs Argenti’s hand. “Help.”
**"You can't run away from this Polaris."**
**"Answer the question Polaris"**
“.........They ended up.. yeah.”
They aren’t going any farther than that.
Argenti saw Mariah's chest seem to inflate
"Was this even real?"
Polaris tried to lean away from Malachite, still bright ass violet. “Nah— Looks like it’s a bunch of nails.”

"Huh? What? What happened?" 
Malachite feigns an innocent tone. 
"I didn't quite catch that."
“.....don’t make me say it.”
"Say what?"
“Mala..”
Malachite cackles again and keeps watching the screen, tossing caramel corn into his mouth.
Polaris internally sighs a huge breath of relief. The show continues on.
....then they get to D’arby Senior.

"You'll have to tell me about it later. I'm curious!"
 Malachite looks up at their face to gauge their reaction.
Polaris just. Lols their head back. Couches are never tall enough for their head to sit back normally, so it kinda just. Hangs there off the edge.
Argenti glared at Polaris. "hey. Don't think you can skip the time you saw a child that was obviously me and didn't know it was me."
Argenti snagged the remote and went to the Alessi episodes
“H-Hey—!”
"As much as I don't want to relive this creep, I want to make fun of Polaris."
"Shut the fuck up Argenti. You thought Jotaro would wear a giant hat for no reason."
(Dumbasses the Lot of them)
“...i’m still the one who saved you, in the end.”

They then watched Baby Pol get bathed by a grown woman

“Wow you really did that huh Polaris” seriya looks over to Polaris, his arms crossed.
“I had nobody else’s souls to bet..”

Malachite gasps dramatically and pulls away from Polaris.

“I was confident..”
It was then time for Hol Horse again
"Oh yeah, I remember Hol Horse showed up again. He stuck his fingers up my nose for some reason."
Then Hol Horse pulled Boingo out of the suitcase
Polaris snickered.
And Argenti nearly spit out his cockolate milk

"You're welcome, Polaris."
As Hol Horse and Boingo's end credits song played, Argenti decided to ask "was anyone else ever thinking about who the other 2 Egyptian God users were before now?"

“...” *Those two mother fuckers haunted my thoughts for 23 years until I inevitably died to Enrico Pucci. I thought they would come back, vengeful and spiteful and so much more powerful, but it turns out that Polnareff was so fucking dumb he managed to use his low IQ to beat them both without realizing it. I’m going to kill him.*
And then pet shop started
"Oh hey we get to hears Iggy's inner thoughts that don't involve farting on me."
“I’ve always felt bad for Iggy. He never wanted to be there.”
"Do you think that this bird made him start giving a shit?"
"Iggy didn't do anything wrong the entire trip. I respect him."
"Also was it just me or were all of Dio's minions named after musical artists?"
“Let’s ignore that.”

Malachite leans his head on Polaris'shoulder.
"Hey Polaris."
“Hm?” Polaris didn’t think much of the contact.
"What would you call Star Platinum if you picked the name yourself? Like, if you had it from birth?"
"Charmy Green, perhaps?"
"It's not green you fucking degenerate."
“....Argenti, shut up.”
“Hm. I’d probably name it something that hard to do with stars, still, because it’s hair looks like a night sky.”
“....Shooting Star.”
"What kind of name is 'Charmy Green' anyway? That's stealing my color-"
Malachite cackles.
Star Platinum puts a hand over Argenti’s mouth before he can even.
And then Kakyoin showed back up with his sunglasses
“...Pointy.” Polaris cringes a little. They never liked those glasses.

"Shooting Star... that's kinda cute actually!" 
Malachite presses his face up against Polaris' side and chuckles as he watches his comeback on the TV.
“...” Polaris stares at Malachite a bit before giving a small smile and turning their attention back to the TV.
"Why did you have those snazzy sunnies anyways?"
"I like the sunglasses. Hey, Polaris, I think I should get some of those."
“No.”
"What? Why?"

Polaris clears their throat, realizing the abrupt response was probably rude. “I.. like the ones you have better. And after Egypt, Kakyoin usually gets a different pair, because of his sight... They’re nice.”
This time, a *healthy* amount of blush appears on Polaris’ cheeks.
Then younger D'Arby showed up
"Aww, what'd they look like?"
Argenti was dreading the Vanilla Ice episodes
“They were small, usually. Sometimes he’d get big round ones, like yours, but a lot of the time they were small rectangular frames. They were cute.”
"Huh... I still like the triangle ones."
“Ok then,” *I guess they’re ok, then.*
There was a small, unusual laugh from Seriya as the Vanilla ice episodes approached. What are they planning.
D'Arby shows his doll collection "Glad I wasn't there for THAT."
Polaris physically shivers. Which Malachite probably feels.

Malachite looks up at him, concerned. 
"Hey, Polaris. You alright?"

Malachite IS TRYING REALLY HARD TO NOT LOSE HIS SHIT

Malachite giggles evilly and drapes himself over Polaris in an evil way
Polaris sighs and leans their head on Malachite’s again.

"W- I didn't do anything?"

Seriya gave a small chuckle. Patting his friend’s back as he looked up to him. “Still, Im super sorry.”
*solus knocks on the door*

"I could." Chariot opened the door
“Ah, okay.” Seriya just goes back to giving Argenti a hug. Hes pretty comfy.
Argenti blushed a little

Malachite stumbles a bit over the threshold and closes the door behind him.
Jesus.
He slips his shoes off, sits down on the couch, and buries his face in his hands.
*Jesus*
Why now? He finally breaks the years of silent yearning between himself and Polaris, and *this* shit happens?
He groans. He won't be surprised if Polaris wants to cut things off after this.
Malachite's eyes widen, and he scrambles out the door. *Oh god.* He bolts for Polaris' house, trying to make out any movement as he runs toward it.
Malachite unlocks the front door with a click and pushes it open with his shoulder, shuffling over to his couch and tossing himself onto it with an *oof.*
He pulls out his phone and taps away at the keyboard with a pleased look on his face.
Polaris knocks on the door, hand in his pockets. He already changed out of what he was wearing at the party— now in a sleeveless turtleneck and baggy jeans.

He rolls off the couch (ow) and opens the door, leaning against the doorframe suggestively.
"Good evening."
He waggles his eyebrows.
He holds back a chuckle at that. “Evening,” he mumbles, leaning down and giving Malachite a small kiss before walking inside.

He grins at the kiss and closes the door before following him.
"Aww, how charming. I've been wooed."
He utters dramatically, draping himself over the couch.
*Drama queen,* he thinks with an eye roll, heading over to the couch and crossing his arms at Malachite. “If I check the kitchen, will I see you bought decent food to live on, or will it be empty?”
"...That depends."
“On what?”
"...On what you consider to be 'decent'."
“...Not just chips and fountain drinks.”
"...There's fruit."
“What kinds?”

He sighs, looking almost sheepish.
"...Cherries."
“...Anything else?”

He sighs again and pauses for a few beats.
"...I *think* I have milk."
